    <!-- Application Structure Plan: A top-down, single-page application that guides the user through a narrative flow. It starts with the diagnosis of the problem, presents the core solution (the interactive funnel), details the strategic tools that support it, covers the necessary technical upgrades, and ends with a clear action plan. This structure was chosen to build a compelling case step-by-step, moving from 'why' to 'what' and 'how', making the complex proposal easily digestible and visually engaging. The interactive funnel is the centerpiece, allowing users to actively explore the new process rather than passively reading about it. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Chaotic old process vs. proposed new one. -> Goal: Organize & Explain. -> Viz/Method: Interactive HTML/CSS process flowchart. -> Interaction: User clicks on a stage to reveal detailed information. -> Justification: Transforms a static table into an engaging, self-paced exploratory tool. -> Library/Method: Vanilla JS + Tailwind.
        - Report Info: Various operational problems (bottlenecks, bad chatbot). -> Goal: Inform. -> Viz/Method: Grid of cards with icons. -> Interaction: Static but visually organized. -> Justification: Breaks down complex problems into scannable, easy-to-understand points. -> Library/Method: Tailwind CSS.
        - Report Info: Need for data tracking (Aging Leads). -> Goal: Demonstrate. -> Viz/Method: Bar chart mockup. -> Interaction: Hover tooltips. -> Justification: Provides a tangible visual example of the data-driven benefits of the new system. -> Library/Method: Chart.js.
        - Report Info: Strategic optimizations (Bot, Nurturing, Governance). -> Goal: Organize. -> Viz/Method: Tabbed interface. -> Interaction: Click to switch content. -> Justification: Neatly organizes multiple related topics without cluttering the page. -> Library/Method: Vanilla JS + Tailwind.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
